[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/pulls/841","id":4109691703,"node_id":"PR_kwDOSeuyxc709Os3","html_url":"https://github.com/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/pull/841","diff_url":"https://github.com/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/pull/841.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/pull/841.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/issues/841","number":841,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"fix(ui): flush a pending RichTextEditor edit on unmount instead of dropping it","user":{"login":"thejesh23","id":35212698,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1MjEyNjk4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/35212698?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/thejesh23","html_url":"https://github.com/thejesh23","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thejesh23/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thejesh23/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thejesh23/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thejesh23/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thejesh23/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thejesh23/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thejesh23/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thejesh23/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thejesh23/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"Fixes #840\n\n## What\n\nThe unmount effect is commented *\"Flush any pending debounce on unmount so the last edit is\nnever lost\"*, but its body only cleared the timer — `emit` was never called from the cleanup,\nso the pending markdown was discarded.\n\n`RichTextEditor` is rendered conditionally (Preview / Edit / Source in `EditableOutput`), so\nswitching view unmounts it. Type, then click Preview within `ONCHANGE_DEBOUNCE_MS` (200 ms),\nand the edit is gone with no error: the parent-owned `value` still holds the pre-keystroke\nmarkdown, the preview/PDF renders stale text, and re-entering Edit re-parses that stale value.\n\n## How\n\nCapture the pending document synchronously in `onUpdate` and serialize **that** in the\ncleanup:\n\n```diff\n+const pendingDocRef = useRef<PMNode | null>(null);\n\n onUpdate: ({ editor: ed }) => {\n   setIsEmpty(ed.isEmpty);\n+  pendingDocRef.current = ed.state.doc;\n   if (debounceRef.current) clearTimeout(debounceRef.current);\n-  debounceRef.current = setTimeout(() => emit(ed), ONCHANGE_DEBOUNCE_MS);\n+  debounceRef.current = setTimeout(() => {\n+    debounceRef.current = undefined;\n+    const doc = pendingDocRef.current;\n+    pendingDocRef.current = null;\n+    if (doc) emitDoc(doc);\n+  }, ONCHANGE_DEBOUNCE_MS);\n },\n```\n\nTwo details worth flagging for review:\n\n- **Why a doc snapshot rather than reading the editor in the cleanup.** A ProseMirror node is\n  immutable, so keeping it is a pointer copy — and it means the flush never has to touch an\n  editor Tiptap may already have destroyed by the time this component's cleanup runs.\n- **No double-emit.** The timer path clears `pendingDocRef` *before* emitting, so an unmount\n  immediately afterwards finds nothing left to send.\n\n`emitDoc` is `useCallback([])`-stable, so `emit` stays stable and the existing\n`useImperativeHandle(ref, …, [editor, emit])` dependency list is unaffected.\n\n## Tests\n\nNew `RichTextEditor.unmountFlush.test.tsx`, driving **real** transactions through the real\neditor via a toolbar command (typing into the ProseMirror surface needs layout APIs jsdom\ndoes not implement; a toolbar command dispatches a genuine transaction, which is all\n`onUpdate` needs):\n\n- an edit made inside the debounce window is emitted when the component unmounts —\n  **fails on `main`** (`expected \"vi.fn()\" to be called 1 times, but got 0 times`);\n- the flush is value-**preserving** for an untouched document, so a plain view switch cannot\n  mark it dirty with different content;\n- a normally-fired debounce still emits exactly once, pinning the no-double-emit property.\n\nWorth noting for the second test: the editor already schedules one emit on mount today —\nloading the initial content is itself a transaction — so a mounted editor emits the unchanged\nvalue after the debounce on `main` too. I verified that on unmodified `main` before writing\nthe assertion, so the test pins \"never emits *different* content\" rather than \"never emits\".\n\n### CI determinism (updated)\n\nThe first revision of this suite was red on a slower CI runner even though it passed locally.\nTwo independent test-only causes, both now fixed (the production change is unchanged):\n\n- **Mount-emit race.** Because loading the initial content schedules a debounce on mount, on a\n  slow runner that mount timer could fire *before* the \"nothing emitted yet\" assertion under\n  real timers. The suite now drains and clears that mount emit before making the edit under\n  test, so the assertion only ever sees the edit's own timer.\n- **Unhandled ProseMirror error.** jsdom implements no layout, so `Range.getClientRects` is\n  `undefined` and ProseMirror's `coordsAtPos → singleRect` throws\n  `target.getClientRects is not a function` from `scrollToSelection` on every transaction — one\n  instance landing in the no-double-emit test. `Range.getClientRects`/`getBoundingClientRect`\n  are now stubbed in the shared `vitest.setup.ts` (next to the existing `scrollIntoView` stub),\n  so editor-driven tests no longer emit that unhandled error.\n\nThe three `unmountFlush` tests pass, with no unhandled errors, across repeated runs.\n\n## Behavior note\n\nBecause the initial-content transaction populates `pendingDocRef`, a **fast mount → unmount**\ninside the debounce window now fires one `onChange` even when the user typed nothing (previously\nthe cleanup only cleared the timer and emitted nothing). The emitted markdown round-trips to the\ninput value, so it is value-preserving — but any autosave or dirty-flag consumer downstream will\nsee that extra, same-value call and should treat a no-op change accordingly.\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [x] `pnpm typecheck` passes (`@ajh/ui`)\n- [x] `eslint --max-warnings 0` clean on the touched files\n- [x] `prettier` clean\n- [x] Tests added\n- [x] No IPC contract change, so no docs update needed\n\n<sub>Note on local verification: the full `pnpm test` run is not green in my sandbox, but the\nfailures are pre-existing on unmodified `main` — 13 files / 146 tests fail with\n`TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'setItem')` (no `localStorage` in this\nenvironment). Verified by checking out clean `main` and re-running. CI is authoritative.</sub>\n\n","created_at":"2026-07-22T15:55:31Z","updated_at":"2026-07-23T02:49:08Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"0f1b84de6d0ce9ea9b611d6c56da074eded1f8a4","assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[{"id":11212541334,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSeuyxc8AAAACnFHNlg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/labels/pkg/ui","name":"pkg/ui","color":"16a085","default":false,"description":"Changes to packages/ui"}],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/pulls/841/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/pulls/841/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/pulls/comments{/number}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/issues/841/comments","statuses_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/saeedkolivand/ai-job-hunter-app/statuses/1d7a3317d2955ab6242d4d7cf7f451060f78f3df","head":{"label":"thejesh23:fix/rich-text-editor-unmount-flush","ref":"fix/rich-text-editor-unmount-flush","sha":"1d7a3317d2955ab6242d4d7cf7f451060f78f3df","user":{"login":"thejesh23","id"